criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria (*applicable to controls):

          1. Must be between 6 and 17 years and 11 months of age*;

          2. Have a diagnosis of MS according to the revised McDonald diagnostic criteria and/or
             International Pediatric MS Study Group criteria;

          3. Has English language knowledge at the level needed to complete clinical questionnaires
             (4th grade level).*

        Exclusion Criteria (*applicable to controls):

          1. Neurological comorbidity.*;

          2. Relapses or requires treatment with steroids within 30 days from enrollment;

          3. Is pregnant at the time of enrollment.*;

          4. Has any metal parts in their body (i.e. Cochlear (ear) implant, metal braces (dental
             fillings are o.k.).*;

          5. Is younger than 6 years of age.*;

          6. Is older than 18 years of age.*;

          7. Has prior history of traumatic brain injury, neurological disorder, cerebral palsy,
             developmental delay or learning disability.*;

          8. Requires sedation for brain scanning.*;

          9. Is claustrophobic, as brain scanning requires children to enter a tunnel in the MRI
             machine.*
